pliSystemName.name: pliSystemName
pliSystemName.description: The sysName of the Access Server. This may be used for diagnostic purposes. This name will be the same as the sysName of the system group of MIB II

psWlanIfTable.name: psWlanIfTable
psWlanIfTable.description: The table contains the information about the wavelan interfaces present in the Access Server.

psWlanIfEntry.name: psWlanIfEntry
psWlanIfEntry.description: The entry in the wavelan interfac table. Described next.

pliWlanIfIndex.name: pliWlanIfIndex
pliWlanIfIndex.description: A unique value for each interface. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

pliWlanIfNetworkName.name: pliWlanIfNetworkName
pliWlanIfNetworkName.description: The network name of this wavelan interface

pliWlanIfMACAddress.name: pliWlanIfMACAddress
pliWlanIfMACAddress.description: The MAC address of the wavelan card present in this interface.

pliWlanIfMediumReservation.name: pliWlanIfMediumReservation
pliWlanIfMediumReservation.description: The medium reservation value. The range is 0 - 2347. Default is 2347 - means disabled. Medium reservation specifies the number of octets in a message above which a RTS/CTS handshake is performed.

pliWlanIfTransmitRate.name: pliWlanIfTransmitRate
pliWlanIfTransmitRate.description: The transmit rate of this interface.

pliWlanIfOperatingFrequency.name: pliWlanIfOperatingFrequency
pliWlanIfOperatingFrequency.description: The RF channel that the Access Server is working on.

pliWlanIfAPDensity.name: pliWlanIfAPDensity
pliWlanIfAPDensity.description: The AP density in the region.

pliWlanIfClosedSystem.name: pliWlanIfClosedSystem
pliWlanIfClosedSystem.description: This flag identifies whether the Access Server will accept associate requests in this interface, from AS-Clients having a network name of 'ANY'. The Access Server should always be a closed station and such requests should always be rejected. This flag is provided for diagnostic purposes.

pliWlanIfAllowedTransmitRates.name: pliWlanIfAllowedTransmitRates
pliWlanIfAllowedTransmitRates.description: This variables reflects the transmit rates that the wavelan card supports

pliWlanIfRegulatoryDomainList.name: pliWlanIfRegulatoryDomainList
pliWlanIfRegulatoryDomainList.description: This variables reflects the regulatory domain the wavelan card belongs to.

pliWlanIfAllowedOperatingFrequencies.name: pliWlanIfAllowedOperatingFrequencies
pliWlanIfAllowedOperatingFrequencies.description: This variables reflects the RF channels that the wavelan card supports.

pliWlanIfCapabilityOptions.name: pliWlanIfCapabilityOptions
pliWlanIfCapabilityOptions.description: The capabilities of the card. Indicates the support of features like WEP.

pliWlanIfProfileCode.name: pliWlanIfProfileCode
pliWlanIfProfileCode.description: The varible conprises of a vendor indication (Lucent or an OEM customer) and a capability indication (eg. bronze or gold).

pliDriverVersion.name: pliDriverVersion
pliDriverVersion.description: The driver's version number. This is a text string including the major and minor release number, and, optionally, the patch level: 'mm.nn.pp', where mm = major release number nn = point release number pp = optional patch number.

psSNMPReadPassword.name: psSNMPReadPassword
psSNMPReadPassword.description: The password for reading object values from the agent.

psSNMPReadWritePassword.name: psSNMPReadWritePassword
psSNMPReadWritePassword.description: The password for reading and modifying object values from the agent.

psSNMPTrapHostIPAddress.name: psSNMPTrapHostIPAddress
psSNMPTrapHostIPAddress.description: The IP address of the host to which traps should be sent.

psSNMPTrapHostPassword.name: psSNMPTrapHostPassword
psSNMPTrapHostPassword.description: The password sent with the trap to enable the management station to ignore unsolicited traps.

psSNMPManagerCount.name: psSNMPManagerCount
psSNMPManagerCount.description: The number of management stations that have been authorised to manage this Access Server.

psSNMPAccessTable.name: psSNMPAccessTable
psSNMPAccessTable.description: The table containing the information about the managers authorised to manage this Access Server.

psSNMPAccessTableEntry.name: psSNMPAccessTableEntry
psSNMPAccessTableEntry.description: The entry in the SNMP access table. Described next.

managerIndex.name: managerIndex
managerIndex.description: Management station identification number. Is the index for the table.

managerIPAddress.name: managerIPAddress
managerIPAddress.description: IP address of the management station.

managerSubnetMask.name: managerSubnetMask
managerSubnetMask.description: The IP subnet mask. Used to grant access to a complete subnet.

managerStatus.name: managerStatus
managerStatus.description: Whether the manager is enabled or disabled. Used to delete the unwanted entries.

psSNMPInBadManagers.name: psSNMPInBadManagers
psSNMPInBadManagers.description: The no of attempts to manage this Access Server by unauthorised managers.

psTestSNMPReadWritePassword.name: psTestSNMPReadWritePassword
psTestSNMPReadWritePassword.description: The password for reading and modifying object values from the agent can be verified by setting this.

psPPPIPAddressAssignmentType.name: psPPPIPAddressAssignmentType
psPPPIPAddressAssignmentType.description: This identifies whether the IP addresses assigned to the AS-Clients are obtained through APM (address pool manager), through DHCP or through the RADIUS server.

psPPPNoOfMACIPMappingEntries.name: psPPPNoOfMACIPMappingEntries
psPPPNoOfMACIPMappingEntries.description: The number of static mapping entries.

psPPPMACIPMappingTable.name: psPPPMACIPMappingTable
psPPPMACIPMappingTable.description: This table contains the static mapping of MAC addresses to IP addresses.

psPPPMACIPMappingTableEntry.name: psPPPMACIPMappingTableEntry
psPPPMACIPMappingTableEntry.description: The entry of the asPPPMACIPMappingTable Described below.

mACIPIndex.name: mACIPIndex
mACIPIndex.description: This is the index for the mappping table.

iPAddress.name: iPAddress
iPAddress.description: The IP address corresponding to the MAC address.

comment.name: comment
comment.description: The comment for this entry, maybe the PC's owner.

entryStatus.name: entryStatus
entryStatus.description: Whether the entry is enabled or disabled. Used to delete the unwanted entries.

psPPPKeepAliveInterval.name: psPPPKeepAliveInterval
psPPPKeepAliveInterval.description: The keep alive interval to be notified to the PPP layer.

psPPPNoOfKeepAliveTimeouts.name: psPPPNoOfKeepAliveTimeouts
psPPPNoOfKeepAliveTimeouts.description: The maximum number of timeouts before the session is torn down.

psPPPPrimaryDNSIPAddress.name: psPPPPrimaryDNSIPAddress
psPPPPrimaryDNSIPAddress.description: The IP address of the primary DNS server in the network.

psPPPSecondaryDNSIPAddress.name: psPPPSecondaryDNSIPAddress
psPPPSecondaryDNSIPAddress.description: The IP address of the secondary DNS server in the network.

psPPPMaxNoOfUsers.name: psPPPMaxNoOfUsers
psPPPMaxNoOfUsers.description: The maximum no of clients permitted to connect to this Access Server.

psPPPCHAPStatus.name: psPPPCHAPStatus
psPPPCHAPStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of CHAP in the Access Server.

psPPPCHAPPriority.name: psPPPCHAPPriority
psPPPCHAPPriority.description: This variable indicates the priority of CHAP among all authentictaion protocols enabled on the Access Server.

psPPPPAPStatus.name: psPPPPAPStatus
psPPPPAPStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of PAP in the Access Server.

psPPPPAPPriority.name: psPPPPAPPriority
psPPPPAPPriority.description: This variable indicates the priority of PAP among all authentictaion protocols enabled on the Access Server.

psPPPPrimaryNBNSIPAddress.name: psPPPPrimaryNBNSIPAddress
psPPPPrimaryNBNSIPAddress.description: The IP address of the Primary NBNS server in the network.

psPPPSecondaryNBNSIPAddress.name: psPPPSecondaryNBNSIPAddress
psPPPSecondaryNBNSIPAddress.description: The IP address of the Secondary NBNS server in the network.

psPPPIPRangeTable.name: psPPPIPRangeTable
psPPPIPRangeTable.description: This table contains the static mapping of MAC addresses to IP addresses.

psPPPIPRangeTableEntry.name: psPPPIPRangeTableEntry
psPPPIPRangeTableEntry.description: The entry of the psPPPIPRangeTable. Described below.

pPPIPIndex.name: pPPIPIndex
pPPIPIndex.description: This is the index for the IP range table.

startIPAddress.name: startIPAddress
startIPAddress.description: This is the staring IP address of this range.

endIPAddress.name: endIPAddress
endIPAddress.description: This is the ending IP address of this range.

width.name: width
width.description: This is the withd of the range (no of addresses).

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the entry, whether to be used or not used. Setting this to delete will remove this entry.

iPComment.name: iPComment
iPComment.description: The comment for this entry may be the PC owner.

psPPPSessionIdleTimeOut.name: psPPPSessionIdleTimeOut
psPPPSessionIdleTimeOut.description: The varible indicates the Session Idle time out.

psVersion.name: psVersion
psVersion.description: The version of the Access Server software currently execuing. Would be text string including the major and minor release number, and, optionally, the patch level: 'mm.nn.pp', where mm = major release number nn = point release number pp = optional patch number.

psIPAddress.name: psIPAddress
psIPAddress.description: The IP address to be assigned to the Access Server (to change from factory fitted IP address).

psSubnetMask.name: psSubnetMask
psSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask of the Access Server.

psDefaultGateway.name: psDefaultGateway
psDefaultGateway.description: The default gateway for the Access Server.

psIPAddressType.name: psIPAddressType
psIPAddressType.description: This can be DHCP/BOOTP(dynamic) or assigned by User via CLI or AS Manager(static). The IP address of the Access Server will be assigned based on this.

psAdministrativeState.name: psAdministrativeState
psAdministrativeState.description: The administrative state of the substation, can be Up or Down.

psTFTPIPAddress.name: psTFTPIPAddress
psTFTPIPAddress.description: The IP address of the TFTP server.

psTFTPFilename.name: psTFTPFilename
psTFTPFilename.description: The filename of the image in the TFTP server.

psTFTPOperation.name: psTFTPOperation
psTFTPOperation.description: The operation to be done, can be upload or download.

psReboot.name: psReboot
psReboot.description: This variable must be set to reboot the Access Server. The value is the number of seconds to wait to do a reboot.

psSecondsToAdminDown.name: psSecondsToAdminDown
psSecondsToAdminDown.description: The count of seconds to go before the administrative state of the Access Server is made down.

psContactEmail.name: psContactEmail
psContactEmail.description: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person.

psBSPBootloaderVersion.name: psBSPBootloaderVersion
psBSPBootloaderVersion.description: This object represents the BSP/Bootloader version that is currently stored in the access server device..

psTelnetSesssions.name: psTelnetSesssions
psTelnetSesssions.description: This object is used to enable or disable telnet access and to specify the number of active telnet sessions. When this object is set to 0, telnet access is disabled. When this object is set to something greater than 0, then it specifies the maximum number of active telnet sessions.

psTelnetPassword.name: psTelnetPassword
psTelnetPassword.description: Password to access Access Server from Telenet.

psTelnetPort.name: psTelnetPort
psTelnetPort.description: The TCP/IP port for Access Server Telenet daemon.

psTelnetTimeout.name: psTelnetTimeout
psTelnetTimeout.description: Telnet inactivity timeout in minutes. The default value is 15 minutes

psTelnetLoginTimeout.name: psTelnetLoginTimeout
psTelnetLoginTimeout.description: Telnet login timeout in seconds. The default value is 30 seconds

psSerialBaudRate.name: psSerialBaudRate
psSerialBaudRate.description: Serial interface baud rate. The default value is 9600

psSerialDataBits.name: psSerialDataBits
psSerialDataBits.description: Serial interface data bits. The default value is 8

psSerialParity.name: psSerialParity
psSerialParity.description: Serial interface Parity check. The default value is None

psSerialStopBits.name: psSerialStopBits
psSerialStopBits.description: Serial interface stop bits. The default value is 1

psSerialFlowControl.name: psSerialFlowControl
psSerialFlowControl.description: Serial interface Flow control. The default value is None

psTFTPFileType.name: psTFTPFileType
psTFTPFileType.description: The type of the file to be uploaded or downloaded to/from the access server. The AllConfigFiles options shall upload or download all the configuration files supported.

psDeviceSerialNumber.name: psDeviceSerialNumber
psDeviceSerialNumber.description: This parameter identifies the serial number of the system.

psBroadcastMessage.name: psBroadcastMessage
psBroadcastMessage.description: This parameter allows to set customized messages to be sent to all connected clients.

psPOSTVersionNumber.name: psPOSTVersionNumber
psPOSTVersionNumber.description: This parameter identifies the POST version number of the system.

psHardwareVersionNumber.name: psHardwareVersionNumber
psHardwareVersionNumber.description: This parameter identifies the Hardware version number of the system.

radiusClientInvalidServerAddresses.name: radiusClientInvalidServerAddresses
radiusClientInvalidServerAddresses.description: The total number of RADIUS Access-Response messages received from unknown addresses since client start-up

radiusServerTable.name: radiusServerTable
radiusServerTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the RADIUS servers with which the client shares a secret.

radiusServerEntry.name: radiusServerEntry
radiusServerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a RADIUS server with which the client shares a secret.

radiusServerIndex.name: radiusServerIndex
radiusServerIndex.description: The RADIUS server with whom the client interacts.

radiusServerType.name: radiusServerType
radiusServerType.description: The RADIUS server type (Authentication or Accounting or Both). For creating a server entry Server Type should be set

radiusServerAddress.name: radiusServerAddress
radiusServerAddress.description: The IP address of the RADIUS server referred to in this table entry.

radiusServerDestPortAuth.name: radiusServerDestPortAuth
radiusServerDestPortAuth.description: The Authentication port of the RADIUS Server.

radiusServerDestPortAcct.name: radiusServerDestPortAcct
radiusServerDestPortAcct.description: The Accounting port of the RADIUS Server.

radiusClientAccessRequests.name: radiusClientAccessRequests
radiusClientAccessRequests.description: The total number of RADIUS Access-Request messages sent since client start-up

radiusClientAccessRetransmissions.name: radiusClientAccessRetransmissions
radiusClientAccessRetransmissions.description: The total number of RADIUS Access-Request messages retransmitted since client start-up

radiusClientAccessAccepts.name: radiusClientAccessAccepts
radiusClientAccessAccepts.description: The total number of RADIUS Access-Accept messages received since client start-up

radiusClientAccessChallenges.name: radiusClientAccessChallenges
radiusClientAccessChallenges.description: The total number of RADIUS Access-Challenge messages received since client start-up

radiusClientMalformedAccessResponses.name: radiusClientMalformedAccessResponses
radiusClientMalformedAccessResponses.description: The total number of malformed RADIUS Access-Response messages received since client start-up

radiusClientAuthenticationBadAuthenticat.name: radiusClientAuthenticationBadAuthenticators
radiusClientAuthenticationBadAuthenticat.description: The total number of RADIUS Access-Response messages containing invalid authenticators received since client start-up

radiusClientAccessRejects.name: radiusClientAccessRejects
radiusClientAccessRejects.description: The total number of RADIUS Access-Reject messages sent since client start-up

radiusClientTimeouts.name: radiusClientTimeouts
radiusClientTimeouts.description: The total number of timeouts since client startup

radiusClientAccountingRequests.name: radiusClientAccountingRequests
radiusClientAccountingRequests.description: The total number of RADIUS Accounting-Request messages sent since client start-up

radiusClientAccountingRetransmissions.name: radiusClientAccountingRetransmissions
radiusClientAccountingRetransmissions.description: The total number of RADIUS Accounting-Request messages retransmitted since client start-up

radiusClientAccountingResponses.name: radiusClientAccountingResponses
radiusClientAccountingResponses.description: The total number of RADIUS Accounting-Response messages received since client start-up

radiusClientAccountingBadAuthenticators.name: radiusClientAccountingBadAuthenticators
radiusClientAccountingBadAuthenticators.description: The total number of RADIUS Accounting-Response messages which contained invalid authenticators received since client start-up

radiusServerSharedSecret.name: radiusServerSharedSecret
radiusServerSharedSecret.description: The secret string which is shared between Server and Client

radiusServerEnabled.name: radiusServerEnabled
radiusServerEnabled.description: Flag to tell whether the server is active or Inactive

radiusServerResponseTime.name: radiusServerResponseTime
radiusServerResponseTime.description: The maximum time within which the server has to respond for a request from the client

radiusServerMaximumRetransmission.name: radiusServerMaximumRetransmission
radiusServerMaximumRetransmission.description: The allowed maximum no. of trials to be tried by a client to get response from the server for a request

psShimECPRetransmissionCount.name: psShimECPRetransmissionCount
psShimECPRetransmissionCount.description: The number of retransmissions when responses are not received with the timeout period.

psShimECPRepeatResponseCount.name: psShimECPRepeatResponseCount
psShimECPRepeatResponseCount.description: The number of time the transmitted response can be retransmitted.

psShimECPRetransmissionTimeout.name: psShimECPRetransmissionTimeout
psShimECPRetransmissionTimeout.description: The timeout interval for a response to be received.

psIappStatus.name: psIappStatus
psIappStatus.description: IAPP Status (whether IAPP feature should be enabled or diaabled)

psIappEndSessOut.name: psIappEndSessOut
psIappEndSessOut.description: Number of IAPP End-PPP session PDUs sent.

psIappEndSessIn.name: psIappEndSessIn
psIappEndSessIn.description: Number of IAPP End-PPP session PDUs received.

psIappEndSessAckOut.name: psIappEndSessAckOut
psIappEndSessAckOut.description: Number of IAPP End-PPP session acknowledgement PDUs sent.

psIappEndSessAckIn.name: psIappEndSessAckIn
psIappEndSessAckIn.description: Number of IAPP End-PPP session acknowledgement PDUs received.

psIappAnnInterval.name: psIappAnnInterval
psIappAnnInterval.description: This parameter represents interval in seconds for performing an IAPP announce operation by the device. The units for this parameter is seconds and default value should be 120 seconds.

psIappAnnRespTime.name: psIappAnnRespTime
psIappAnnRespTime.description: This parameter indicates the amount of time in seconds the device waits to send an IAPP announce response after an announce request message is sent. This parameter is set to a default value of 2 seconds and is not configurable.

psIappHandOvrTimeOut.name: psIappHandOvrTimeOut
psIappHandOvrTimeOut.description: This parameter represents the time in milliseconds the device waits before it resends a handover response message. The default value for this parameter should be 512 milliseconds.

psIappMaxHandOvrRetries.name: psIappMaxHandOvrRetries
psIappMaxHandOvrRetries.description: This parameter indicates the maximum amount of retransmission sent by the device for a handover request message. The default for this parameter should be 2.

psIappRoamingClients.name: psIappRoamingClients
psIappRoamingClients.description: Number of roaming clients currently attached to the Access Server.

psIpxStatus.name: psIpxStatus
psIpxStatus.description: Which protocol is supported, i.e, IP or IPX or both IP and IPX.

psIpxDefaultRouterNodeNum.name: psIpxDefaultRouterNodeNum
psIpxDefaultRouterNodeNum.description: If the source IPX network number is not equal to the destination IPX Network number in the packet from wireless side to the wired side, then replace the destination Ether MAC addr with the value of this object (Default IPX router node number).

psIpxWiredToWlessBridged.name: psIpxWiredToWlessBridged
psIpxWiredToWlessBridged.description: Number of packets bridged from wired side to wireless side.

psIpxWlessToWiredBridged.name: psIpxWlessToWiredBridged
psIpxWlessToWiredBridged.description: Number of packets bridged from wiredless side to wired side.

psIpxEthernetEncapsulationFormat.name: psIpxEthernetEncapsulationFormat
psIpxEthernetEncapsulationFormat.description: Encapsulation type to be used for the IPX packets sent in wired side

psASClientTable.name: psASClientTable
psASClientTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the ASClients (IPX) connected to the access server 2000 device.

psASClientEntry.name: psASClientEntry
psASClientEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a ASClient (IPX) connnected to the Access Server 2000 device.

psPPPSessionId.name: psPPPSessionId
psPPPSessionId.description: The PPP Session ID assigned by the AS-2000 to this ASClient.

psIpxClientNetworkNumber.name: psIpxClientNetworkNumber
psIpxClientNetworkNumber.description: The IPX Node Number assigned by the Novell Server to this IPX client.

psIpxClientMAC.name: psIpxClientMAC
psIpxClientMAC.description: The Wireless MAC of this IPX Client.

psIpxClientStatus.name: psIpxClientStatus
psIpxClientStatus.description: Flag to indicate whether the IPX Client is Active or Inactive. IPX Client status can also be disabled/enabled/deleted.

psASClientSessionUpTime.name: psASClientSessionUpTime
psASClientSessionUpTime.description: This object represents the session up time for each AS Client or PPP virttual interface.

psASClientPacketsIn.name: psASClientPacketsIn
psASClientPacketsIn.description: This object represents the number of packets (unicast and non-unicast)recieved for each AS Client or PPP virttual interface.

psASClientPacketsOut.name: psASClientPacketsOut
psASClientPacketsOut.description: This object represents the number of packets (unicast and non-unicast)sent for each AS Client or PPP virttual interface.

oriLinkTestTimeOut.name: oriLinkTestTimeOut
oriLinkTestTimeOut.description: The value of this parameter determines the time that a link test will continue without any SNMP requests for a Link Test Table entry. When the time expires the Link Test Table is cleared.

oriLinkTestInterval.name: oriLinkTestInterval
oriLinkTestInterval.description: This parameter indicates the interval (in millisec) between sending link test frames to a station. Default on 200 millisecond.

oriLinkTestExplore.name: oriLinkTestExplore
oriLinkTestExplore.description: When this parameter is set to 2, the access point will send out an explore request on all 802.11 interfaces and from the results build the Link Test table. This table is valid only while this parameter is 3.

oriLinkTestTable.name: oriLinkTestTable
oriLinkTestTable.description: This table contains the information for the stations currently associated with this access point.

oriLinkTestTableEntry.name: oriLinkTestTableEntry
oriLinkTestTableEntry.description: This parameter represents the entry in the Remote Link Test table.This is described below.

oriLinkTestTableIndex.name: oriLinkTestTableIndex
oriLinkTestTableIndex.description: This parameter represents a unique value for each stattion. The value for each station must remain constant at least from one explore to the next.

oriLinkTestInProgress.name: oriLinkTestInProgress
oriLinkTestInProgress.description: When this parameter is set to 2 the access point will initiate a link test sequence with this station.

oriLinkTestStationName.name: oriLinkTestStationName
oriLinkTestStationName.description: This parameter identifies the name of the station whom which the link test is being performed.

oriLinkTestMACAddress.name: oriLinkTestMACAddress
oriLinkTestMACAddress.description: This variable represents the MAC address that will be mapped to the IP Address of the station.

oriLinkTestStationProfile.name: oriLinkTestStationProfile
oriLinkTestStationProfile.description: This parameter represents the profile/capabilities for this station.

oriLinkTestOurCurSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurCurSignalLevel
oriLinkTestOurCurSignalLevel.description: The current signal level (in dB)for the link test from this station. This variable indicates the running average of the local signal level using the algorithm (3/4*oldvalue + 1/4*newvalue).

oriLinkTestOurCurNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurCurNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestOurCurNoiseLevel.description: The current noise level (in dB)for the link test to this station. This variable indicates the running average of the local noise level.

oriLinkTestOurCurSNR.name: oriLinkTestOurCurSNR
oriLinkTestOurCurSNR.description: The current signal to noise ratio for the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMinSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurMinSignalLevel
oriLinkTestOurMinSignalLevel.description: The minimum signal level during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMinNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurMinNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestOurMinNoiseLevel.description: The minimum noise level during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMinSNR.name: oriLinkTestOurMinSNR
oriLinkTestOurMinSNR.description: The minimum signal to noise ratio during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMaxSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurMaxSignalLevel
oriLinkTestOurMaxSignalLevel.description: The maximum signal level during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMaxNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestOurMaxNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestOurMaxNoiseLevel.description: The maximum noise level during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMaxSNR.name: oriLinkTestOurMaxSNR
oriLinkTestOurMaxSNR.description: The maximum signal to noise ratio during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurLowFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestOurLowFrameCount
oriLinkTestOurLowFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 1 Mbit/s speed during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurStandardFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestOurStandardFrameCount
oriLinkTestOurStandardFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 2 Mbit/s speed during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurMediumFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestOurMediumFrameCount
oriLinkTestOurMediumFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 5.5 Mbit/s (for Turbo-8, it is 5 Mbit/s) speed during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestOurHighFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestOurHighFrameCount
oriLinkTestOurHighFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 11 Mbit/s (for Turbo-8, it is 8 Mbit/s) speed during the link test to this station.

oriLinkTestHisCurSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisCurSignalLevel
oriLinkTestHisCurSignalLevel.description: The current signal level for the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisCurNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisCurNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestHisCurNoiseLevel.description: The current noise level for the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisCurSNR.name: oriLinkTestHisCurSNR
oriLinkTestHisCurSNR.description: The current signal to noise ratio for the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisMinSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisMinSignalLevel
oriLinkTestHisMinSignalLevel.description: The minimum signal level during the link test to the remote statio or access point.

oriLinkTestHisMinNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisMinNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestHisMinNoiseLevel.description: The minimum noise level during the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisMinSNR.name: oriLinkTestHisMinSNR
oriLinkTestHisMinSNR.description: The minimum signal to noise ratio during the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisMaxSignalLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisMaxSignalLevel
oriLinkTestHisMaxSignalLevel.description: The maximum signal level during the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisMaxNoiseLevel.name: oriLinkTestHisMaxNoiseLevel
oriLinkTestHisMaxNoiseLevel.description: The maximum noise level during the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisMaxSNR.name: oriLinkTestHisMaxSNR
oriLinkTestHisMaxSNR.description: The maximum signal to noise ratio during the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisLowFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestHisLowFrameCount
oriLinkTestHisLowFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 1 Mbit/s speed during the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisStandardFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestHisStandardFrameCount
oriLinkTestHisStandardFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 2 Mbit/s speed during the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisMediumFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestHisMediumFrameCount
oriLinkTestHisMediumFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 5.5 Mbit/s (for Turbo-8, it is 5 Mbit/s) speed during the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestHisHighFrameCount.name: oriLinkTestHisHighFrameCount
oriLinkTestHisHighFrameCount.description: The total number of frames sent at 11 Mbit/s (for Turbo-8, it is 5 Mbit/s) speed during the link test to the remote station or access point.

oriLinkTestInterface.name: oriLinkTestInterface
oriLinkTestInterface.description: The PCMCIA Card Number to which the Client has sent the Explore Response Message.

oriLinkTestRadioType.name: oriLinkTestRadioType
oriLinkTestRadioType.description: The Wireless Standard eg. IEEE 802.11 or IEEE 802.11b used on the Radio.

accessServerGenericInformationMessage.name: accessServerGenericInformationMessage
